In order to simulate virus mutation in small world network, SIR model is modified and its dynamic process is evolved by discrete steps. In small world network, each vertex has three states, namely S, I and R state. A vertex is in S state before being infected. If it is infected, it goes into an infection cycle \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
