To further justify the mutation-immune model, the present mutation-immune model is compared with the mutation model proposed by Girvan et al. [31]. They proposed a bitstring model in which pathogen strains are represented by bitstrings, where the bitstring is regarded as an abstract representation of a pathogen’s genetic code. Hosts are immune to infection by pathogens that are highly similar to pathogens with which they have been previously infected, where similarity between two strains are measured by hamming distance \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
