				\begin{document}$$2^{l}$$\end{document}2l possible bitstrings of fixed length l. Individuals keep a record of all the strains with which they have been infected, and these histories are defined as their memory repertoire. In every time step, each infected individual exposes z others by selecting individuals uniformly at random from the entire population. The susceptibility of a contacted individual is determined by comparing the bitstring of the challenge strain with the bitstrings of all strains in the memory repertoire. Specifically, an individual is susceptible if \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
